1. The width of the Provincial and Municipal roads abutting the lot applied for must have the minimum right-of-way reservation to comply with the mandatory provision of Executive Order No. 113, series of 1955;

2. That all waterways passing thru or adjoining the said lot be considered parts of the public domain and be subject to the mandatory provision of Presidential Decree No. 296 and Presidential Decree No. 1067; and

3. That the 3-meters wide public easement along Calinog Creek reckoned from the lines reached by the highest flood which does not cause inundation be excluded from the areas applied for pursuant to Section 28 of the implementing rules and regulations of PD 1067 in relation to Article 51 of said Decree.

NOTE:

This lot is identical to Lot 35563, a consolidation and subdivision of Lots 22269 and 22270, Csd-13010, formerly a portion of Lot 4932, Cad-237.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

Done in the City of Manila, this 2nd day of November, in the year of Our Lord, nineteen hundred and eighty-seven.

(Sgd.) CORAZON C. AQUINO

By the President: (Sgd.) CATALINO MACARAIG, JR. Acting Executive Secretary

